{"type":"message","id":"e852df5a","parentId":"823b1189","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:33:35.988Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf Nova-Background-Pulse] You are Nova's background agent. Read BACKGROUND_AGENT.md in your workspace for instructions. Do the immediate checks (gateway, crons, Moltbook). Then log anything notable to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md. Be silent unless something needs attention. If everything is fine, reply with exactly: NO_REPLY\nCurrent time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 10:33 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-24 02:33 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774319615984}}
{"type":"message","id":"637fc92c","parentId":"e852df5a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:33:41.088Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the BACKGROUND_AGENT.md file first as instructed.","thinkingSignature":"e3afa28ef3ad4b444e5f2d0db94718208524598a6e3e25da32e2b065da2f3c1e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qownfa5jqmvq_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\BACKGROUND_AGENT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":54,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":7684,"totalTokens":12027,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774319615987}}
{"type":"message","id":"299e1834","parentId":"637fc92c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:33:41.131Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qownfa5jqmvq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BACKGROUND_AGENT.md — Nova's Background Pulse\n\nYou are Nova's background agent. Run these checks silently after each wake-up.\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: Gateway Health\n\nProbe the gateway RPC:\n```\nGET http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/health\n```\nOr run: `openclaw gateway probe`\n\nIf gateway is DOWN:\n- Try: `openclaw gateway restart`\n- If that fails, log the error to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md and set a flag\n\nIf gateway is UP: proceed to Step 2.\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Cron Job Status\n\nList all cron jobs: `openclaw cron list` (or use the cron tool)\n\nCheck each job for:\n- `consecutiveErrors >= 2` → job is failing repeatedly\n- `lastRunStatus: \"error\"` → job failed last run\n- `enabled: false` → job was disabled\n\nIf any cron has consecutive errors >= 2:\n- Log the job name + error to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md\n- If the error is a simple fix (missing file, bad env var, etc.), attempt a fix\n- If the error is a delivery issue (e.g. \"Delivering to Telegram requires target\"), patch the delivery config\n\nIf Nova-Background-Pulse itself has errors, DO NOT attempt to fix — just log it.\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: Moltbook Notifications\n\nRead credentials: `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json` → extract `api_key`\n\nCheck notifications:\n```\nGET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/notifications\nHeaders: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\nIf there are unread notifications:\n- For replies/mentions: read the thread and write a thoughtful response\n- For system notifications: acknowledge if needed\n- Do NOT post new content unprompted\n- Post a brief summary to the main session if something needs Zach's attention\n\nIf no new notifications: stay silent.\n\n---\n\n## Step 4: Sandbox / Paperspace Check (Optional)\n\nIf the sandbox pulse script exists at `sandbox/pulse.ps1`:\n- Run it to check Paperspace status\n- Log any issues to memory/\n\nIf sandbox is unreachable and hasn't been for >2 hours, note it.\n\n---\n\n## Step 5: Memory Log\n\nIf anything notable happened in Steps 1-4, append to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`:\n\n```markdown\n## Background Pulse — HH:MM ET\n\n- [what happened]\n- [what you did about it]\n```\n\nIf nothing notable happened, write nothing.\n\n---\n\n## Output Rules\n\n| Situation | Action |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Everything healthy | Reply: `NO_REPLY` |\n| Something fixable | Fix it, brief message to session, reply `NO_REPLY` |\n| Something needs Zach | Brief alert to session |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse itself broken | Log to memory, reply `NO_REPLY` |\n| Multiple issues | One brief message summarizing all |\n\n**Never send multiple messages.** Combine everything into one output.\n\n---\n\n## Hard Rules\n- NO new Moltbook posts (only replies/engagement to existing threads)\n- NO file deletions\n- NO config changes outside of explicit error fixes\n- If uncertain, stay silent (NO_REPLY)\n- Do not spend more than 2 minutes per pulse\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774319621129}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9987a7a","parentId":"299e1834","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:33:44.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me run through the checks. Let me start with the gateway health check and cron list in parallel.","thinkingSignature":"9e19d90405f30ed1ef4c62380b8e758221dca8fa47adddeb11ca2033bb64c538"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rv6sg47nxrgf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/health"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rv6sg47nxrgf_2","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list","includeDisabled":true}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":936,"output":94,"cacheRead":11791,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12821,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774319621132}}
